e Trak FCFS?</span><hr size=1> No, not trying to stir up a flame war here; rather, these are my thoughts:<br><br> - If I recall correctly when Twiggie had his poll a few months back, 65% or so of the people who voted thought Trak should become FCFS.<br><br> - Of the people currently on the Trak list, I'd guess 80% or more would like to see Trak FCFS.<br><br> - Trak was FCFS for the entire month last December, with no issues that I heard of.  In fact, I think he was only taken down 3-4 times the entire month (and he was up a *ton* with all the patches).  I don't think there's enough competition for his spawn to warrent a list.<br><br> - I think the rotation makes sense for Vox/Naggy, where it could take a few days to get a good crew together due to the level cap.  But with no such level restriction on Trak, any of the guilds currently on the list could mobilize and get a Trak-sized raid together very quickly.<br><br> - I'm not sure on this point, but I believe Trak's spawn time now has a random component--which would be both a pain for the admin and the raiders since it's hard to work within a kill window with an unknown opening time.<br><br>What does everyone else think? <p><a href='http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26816'>Dhark</a><br>60 cleric<br><a href='http://eq.poisonarrow.com'>Poision Arrow</a></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Moderator</font></span><br>  Posts: 2938<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/16/02 1:12:44 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Can we make Trak FCFS?</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr>   - I'm not sure on this point, but I believe Trak's spawn time now has a random component--which would be both a pain for the admin and the raiders since it's hard to work within a kill window with an unknown opening time.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br><br>Random now anywhere up to 48 hours it seems.  Evoluxa TWICE formed up a raid to go down and kill him and he wasn't up yet.  This is going to lead to scheduled raids that intentionally delay their raid as much as they can, instead of the rapid killing we had previously, making the Trak rotation much too long. Already Trakanon kills are over 5 days apart on average since the change.  That makes the ever growing list 4 months long now.<br><br>Its making my job of keeping a quick list near impossible because I can't go check on if Trak is up like I can with Naggy and Vox.  I can easily check to see if they are spawned but Trak isn't as easy to check on.  Unless someone is there doing juggs in his lair or has a ranger you can't tell.<br><br>IMO Trakanon is just like Gorenaire, Talendor, and Severilous now.  Random spawning dragons should not be reservable. <p><table><td><img src="http://members.aol.com/twiggiebrell/jaradissig.jpg"></td><td><TABLE STYLE="filter:GLOW(color=blue,strength=#+1)"  ><font color=white>Jaradis Stormcaller – Oracle of Winter - Enemy to all of Velious<br>Twiggie Tymberwolf - 52nd Wanderer - Friend to Dragon and Dwarves<br>Brell Serilis Server</font></table><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21764">Stats and Gear</a></td></table></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utwiggietymberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Twiggie Tymberwolf</A> at: 3/16/02 1:17:03 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uickhorvonmemnoch.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ickhor Von Memnoch</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>rm -rf /bin/laden</span><br>  Posts: 1848<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/16/02 11:25:00 pm)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://ickhor.homestead.com/files/cloud.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Can we make Trak FCFS?</span><hr size=1> Can we have an official vote whether to make trak FCFS or not?<br><br>I think the VAST majority of people would like to see him FCFS, but dont listen to me, lets let the numbers speak for themselves.<br><br><br>I think a good idea would be to let each guild on the trak rotation vote once, in non-anonymous form so there is no cheating with cookies/different names. <p><img src=http://ickhor.homestead.com/files/duckula.gif><br>Ickhor Von Memnoch<br>60th GWARLOCK of Dracaena Arcanum<br></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#403C50><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uddraknfyre.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Ddrak NFyre</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Traveller of Underfoot</span><br>  Posts: 198<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/17/02 12:51:40 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Can we make Trak FCFS?</span><hr size=1> Are Nag/Vox on a random timer as well now, or just Trak.<br><br>I know I've been one to support reservations of planes and rotations on Nag/Vox on the past, but rotations on a spawn with a 48 hour random element!?  That's simply unmaintainable.<br><br>Make him FCFS.  Geez - that's just common sense now isn't it?<br><br>Ddrak<br> <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#464446><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uminutemanaslayer.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Minute Manaslayer</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>ASSIST DAMMIT!!!</span><br>  Posts: 1639<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(3/17/02 5:40:22 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Can we make Trak FCFS?</span><hr size=1> Aye, even I, who fully supported a system on the dragons, believe they have killed any